  urldate = {2023-08-16},
  abstract = {Overview Software Description Websites Readings Courses ~OverviewHotspot analysis is a spatial analysis and mapping technique interested in the identification of clustering of spatial phenomena. These spatial phenomena are depicted as points in a map and refer to locations of events or objects.DescriptionA hotspot can be defined as an area that has higher concentration of events compared to the expected number given a random distribution of events. Hotspot detection evolved from the study of point distributions or spatial arrangements of points in a space (Chakravorty, 1995).},
